<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="redescription">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Redescription</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
(based on lectotype and additional specimens from the type locality, Syria, and Israel). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Male.</emphasis>
Head. Antennae black to dark brown; basoflagellomere elongated ca. two times as long as wide, and 2.2-2.5 times as long as pedicel, concave dorsally with acute apex; large fossette dorsolateral and dorsomedial; arista dark and thickened at basal one third, covered with dense microtrichia, 1.6-1.7 times as long as basoflagellomere (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Antenna. A Merodon hirsutus, outer side, lateral view, male B Merodon hirsutus, inner side, lateral view, male C Merodon hirsutus, dorsal view, male D Merodon hirsutus, outer side, lateral view, female E Merodon kawamurae, outer side, lateral view, male F Merodon kawamurae, inner side, lateral view, male G Merodon kawamurae, dorsal view, male H Merodon kawamurae, outer side, lateral view, female I Merodon medium sp. nov., outer side, lateral view, male J Merodon medium sp. nov., outer side, lateral view, female. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377380" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">19A-C</figureCitation>
); face black with gray microtrichia, covered with whitish pile; frons mostly shiny, with yellowish gray pile; oral margin microtrichose, with small, shiny lateral area; lunule shiny black, bare; eye contiguity 12-14 facets long; vertex isosceles, with long, pale whitish yellow pile, mixed with black pile on the ocellar triangle; ocellar triangle equilateral; occiput with gray-yellow pile; eyes covered with dense pile (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Head, dorsal view. A Merodon hirsutus, male B Merodon hirsutus, female C Merodon opacus sp. nov., male. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377381" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">20A</figureCitation>
); vertical triangle: eye contiguity: frons = 1.4: 1: 2.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377381" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" start="Figure 20" startId="F20">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Figure 20.</emphasis>
